Posted! A link has been posted to your Facebook feed. Join the Conversation Prep Sports Ethan Bernal , Montgomery Advertiser 3:35 p.m. CDT October 25, 2015 
There was no shortage of points this week, and as a result, multiple players put up big numbers to help their teams to victory. Here’s who was selected as the Advertiser All-Metro Players of the Week for Week 10 (Oct. 22-23). Buy Photo 
Lee quarterback Shaquille Johnson throws against Prattville at Stanley Jensen Stadium in Prattville, Ala. on Friday October 23, 2015. (Photo: Mickey Welsh / Advertiser) 
CLASS 5A-7A 
Shaquille Johnson, QB, Sr., Robert E. Lee 
Johnson completed 14-of-24 passes for 349 yards and three touchdowns in the Generals’ 48-28 win over Prattville. He also added 12 carries for 46 yards and two touchdowns. 
Lee (6-3) travels to Wetumpka on Friday. Buy Photo 
Montgomery Academy's Keefe White (22) is stopped by Trinity's Marshall Dean at the Montgomery Academy campus in Montgomery Al. on Friday September 25, 2015. (Photo: Mickey Welsh / Advertiser) 
CLASS 1A-4A 
Keefe White, RB, So., Montgomery Academy 
White ran for 235 yards and three touchdowns in the Eagles’ 57-3 victory over Prattville Christian. 
MA (8-1) travels to Alabama Christian on Friday. 
Autauga Academy’s Joseph Burke. (Photo: CONTRIBUTED) 
AISA 
Joseph Burke, RB, Sr., Autauga Academy 
Burke scored five touchdowns in the Generals’ 55-0 win over Crenshaw Christian. He ran for 60 yards and two touchdowns, caught for 96 yards and two scores and returned a kickoff 65 yards for a touchdown. 
Autauga Academy (5-4) hosts Lowndes Academy on Friday. Read or Share this story: http://on.mgmadv.com/1N1eBoG Most Popular
